<p>Algorithms that use depth-first search as a building block include:
</p>
<ul><li>Finding <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Connected_componen=
t_(graph_theory)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Connected component (graph=
 theory)">connected components</a>.</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topological_sorting" title=3D"=
Topological sorting">Topological sorting</a>.</li>
<li>Finding 2-(edge or vertex)-connected components.</li>
<li>Finding 3-(edge or vertex)-connected components.</li>
<li>Finding the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bridge_(graph_theo=
ry)#Bridge-finding_algorithm" title=3D"Bridge (graph theory)">bridges</a> o=
f a graph.</li>
<li>Generating words in order to plot the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Limit_set" title=3D"Limit set">limit set</a> of a <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Group_(mathematics)" title=3D"Group (mathematics)">=
group</a>.</li>
<li>Finding <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strongly_connected_com=
ponents" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Strongly connected components">stro=
ngly connected components</a>.</li>
<li>Determining whether a species is closer to one species or another in a =
phylogenetic tree.</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Planarity_testing" title=3D"Pl=
anarity testing">Planarity testing</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-9" class=3D"refe=
rence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Depth-first_search#cite_not=
e-9"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>9<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-10" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Depth-first_search#cite_note-10"><span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">[</span>10<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>Solving puzzles with only one solution, such as <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Maze" title=3D"Maze">mazes</a>. (DFS can be adapted to fi=
nd all solutions to a maze by only including nodes on the current path in t=
he visited set.)</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maze_generation" class=3D"mw-r=
edirect" title=3D"Maze generation">Maze generation</a> may use a randomized=
 DFS.</li>
<li>Finding <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biconnected_graph" tit=
le=3D"Biconnected graph">biconnectivity in graphs</a>.</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Primogeniture#Absolute_primoge=
niture" title=3D"Primogeniture">Succession</a> to the throne shared by the =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Commonwealth_realms" class=3D"mw-r=
edirect" title=3D"Commonwealth realms">Commonwealth realms</a>.<sup id=3D"c=
ite_ref-11" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/De=
pth-first_search#cite_note-11"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>11<span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li></ul>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Complexity">Complexity</h2>=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</sp=
an><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DDepth-first_sear=
ch&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D7" title=3D"Edit section: Complexity"><s=
pan>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></=
div>
<p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analysis_of_algorithms" tit=
le=3D"Analysis of algorithms">computational complexity</a> of DFS was inves=
tigated by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Reif" title=3D"Joh=
n Reif">John Reif</a>. More precisely, given a graph <span class=3D"mwe-mat=
h-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mw=
e-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.o=
rg/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle G}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
